=====test bug 11914091 =======
explain select /*+parallel(t1, 2) leading(t1 t2) use_hash(t2) px_join_filter(t2)*/t1.c1, f1() from t1 join t2 on t1.c1=t2.c1 order by t2.c1;
Query Plan
===============================================================
|ID|OPERATOR                       |NAME|EST.ROWS|EST.TIME(us)|
---------------------------------------------------------------
|0 |SORT                           |    |2       |15          |
|1 |└─HASH JOIN                    |    |2       |15          |
|2 |  ├─DISTRIBUTED TABLE FULL SCAN|t1  |51      |4           |
|3 |  └─DISTRIBUTED TABLE FULL SCAN|t2  |1       |3           |
===============================================================
Outputs & filters:
-------------------------------------
  0 - output([t1.c1], [f1()]), filter(nil)
      sort_keys([t2.c1, ASC])
  1 - output([t2.c1], [t1.c1]), filter(nil)
      equal_conds([t1.c1 = t2.c1]), other_conds(nil)
  2 - output([t1.c1]), filter(nil)
      access([t1.c1]), partitions(p0)
      is_index_back=false, is_global_index=false, 
      range_key([t1.__pk_increment]), range(MIN ; MAX)always true
  3 - output([t2.c1]), filter(nil)
      access([t2.c1]), partitions(p0)
      is_index_back=false, is_global_index=false, 
      range_key([t2.__pk_increment]), range(MIN ; MAX)always true
